rComments: Curtis might appear OTT at times but she is passionate about accounting. Despite seemingly endless assignments, HALF the points do come outside of tests! With 100+ points in EC, and highly repetitive questions on tests, the class could NOT be EASIER; just keep up with the readings and attend lecs for open book quizzes.I am a PS major but got an A+

Class is 1.5hrs and she talks about so much random stuff then hurries at the end of lecture to put in all the needed material. Expect to do bad in her exams; your not graded on whether you know the material, your grade is based on whether you know how to take an exam or not.

curtis is a horrible teacher...literally every class she is crazy and goes on and on about pointless stuff..rarely teachers useful material..if she actually would teach accounting we would get out of class 40 minutes earlier...i dont understand how UofI accounting is ranked so high with her as a teacher, oh ya be prepared for mistakes on tests/quiz
Susan is not that orthodox with her teachings. She someone that would talk about whatever she feel like in class but expect you to learn on your own. Good luck on the tests/exams ...

A very lazy professor. Copied half of last year's final from the book word for word.  Tries to make the class funny and fails. Instead she could actually teach and make class shorter. It's hard to actually pay attention when she does teach, because those moments are few and far between.  Don't point out flaws in her "system" because she will yell.

Damn...she loves this word.... Strong bias and disorganized on what she want students know...don't like her. I really don't think a good professor is the one who judge people differently.  she is kind of crazy everyday....and most of time, it is annoying. WORST PROFESSOR IN UIUC...

At times, I think she is completely crazy, useless, but then at other times I think she really cares and means well. She teaches you more about life lessons than about accounting itself. Don't expect to be enlightened about accounting after this class. The extra credit will get you through this class and she curves it a ton.

Ignore the previous negative comments. Curtis was an extremely nice and devoted professor. She gave tons of extra time to help all those who truly wanted to learn. I wish they were more teachers enthusiastic like her. I did not suggest a New Professor on my ICES form unanimously like AKPsi. I know they did this because I was a pledge in the spring.

First half of the semester was completely useless, you only begin accounting once half the semester has gone by, and then you you finish off with more nonsense.  Saying that the exams are subjective is the understatement of the year.  Sitting through an hour and a half lecture is painful, but you go for the extra credit.  Final was bizarre.

The first half of the class is completely useless, it is only when half the semester has gone by that you begin accounting, and then you finish off with more nonsense at the end.  Saying her exams are subjective is the understatement of the year.  Sitting an hour and a half in class is painful, but you go for the extra credit.  Final was bizarre.

At first she comes across as goofy and fun, doing splits in class and swearing like she's 10 again. But then it gets old and you realize she's the idiot you thought she was. I don't understand why she's still teaching when her tests are incoherent and full of mistakes. Too bad you have to stick with her if you enroll in business.

If you do all the required readings this class is easy.  Also, go to office hours and talk to Professor Curtis.  She is one of the nicest and funniest professors I've ever had.  Do the work, and the rest will fall into place.

Terrible class, it's unfortunate there is only one teacher for
 it, because she is an idiot. 90 minute long lectures that could easily be cut down to 30. Extremely disorganized, material covered in class barely pertains to the material on the exams. She is a horrible excuse for a teacher and her tests are full
 of mistakes due to her incompetence.
Presents the material in a convoluted manner. Deliberately puts multiple answers that could be correct on the tests, but only accepts her version. Overall a very poor teacher.
She's an absolutely horrible professor.  It should be fairly straight forward material but she wastes time singing and dancing instead of teaching.
awful, can't write a test. can't teach a lecture.  material is very easy but she purposefully makes it difficult.  lots of extra credit

The worst teacher I have had in my 4 years at U of I.  I took this class as a senior and was suprised by how awful she was.  She doesn't teach anything.  I was looking forward to learning basics of accounting but unfortunately I didnt.  Discussion lasted 10 mins at the most.  Lots of extra credit  If you are looking for a good laugh take this class

As many others have said, Her lectures are really disorganized and hard to follow. Most students only show up on the off chance that she decides to give extra credit that day. The textbook is barely used until the very end of the semester when you have to literally memorize a few passages. Be sure to memorize exam questions, they will show up again
Wasn't a good experience but I did end up learning something from the course. The way she tests us on material is definitely not fair but I ended up with an A-.

still don't know what the hell I learned this semester. worst teach-yourself style I've ever seen. Half of the final exam was on information either sparsely covered or simply not covered at all. I have a lot of previous accounting experience but was still only to scrape a B+ from this crazy woman. too bad shes the only professor for 201.
